==Swedish==
===Noun===
'''sne(d)fitta '''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPA|/ˈsneːˌfɪta/}}
#(''slang, may be considered vulgar'') part of a [[cigarette]] which is burning unevenly due to being rolled or lit improperly; [[run]], [[runner]]
#:''Nu har du rullat en cigg som fått '''sne(d)fitta''' igen.''
#:"Now you rolled another ciggarette that got a runner."

====Etymology====
At least since the early 1990s. From ''[[sned]]'' "crooked; uneven" and ''[[fitta]]'' "cunt".

